# Specific to ASP.NET Core
# Ignore appsettings files containing sensitive data
DiligenciaProveedores.Api/appsettings.json
DiligenciaProveedores.Api/appsettings.*.json

# IMPORTANT: If you want specific environment appsettings.json files (like appsettings.Production.json
# or appsettings.Development.json) to be committed, you need to add exceptions.
# Example:
#!appsettings.Development.json # Uncomment this line if you want appsettings.Development.json to be tracked
#!appsettings.Production.json  # Uncomment this line if you want appsettings.Production.json to be tracked

# For now, I recommend letting appsettings.*.json catch all and manually configuring in Azure,
# or uncommenting only appsettings.Production.json if it contains public URLs/placeholders.

